---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Travel guides and photography from real experience — built to help you explore smarter."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="page">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h1>About Globe &amp; Frame</h1>

      <h2>Why Travel</h2>
      <p>
        Travel has a way of opening your eyes to new cultures, new cuisines, and new perspectives.
        It is why I always encourage friends and family to go see the world for themselves.
      </p>
      <p>
        We all share one planet, but the best way to truly understand it is by experiencing it firsthand.
        That is why I write, photograph, and share my experiences. My goal is to pass along what I have
        learned and help others travel smarter, discover incredible destinations, and feel more confident
        exploring the world.
      </p>

      <h2>About Me</h2>
      <p>
        I live in New York City with my faithful German Shorthair Pointer, Daisy. I find just as much joy
        in cooking at home as I do in dining out. Exploring cities, beaches, photography, paddle boarding,
        skiing, and uncovering excellent Italian cuisine are some of my favorite pastimes.
      </p>
      <p>
        In summing up my travel style&hellip; I can savor a Bud Light in the Redneck Riviera just as much as
        a glass of ros&eacute; in the French Riviera. My blog embodies a certain <em>je ne sais quoi</em>.
      </p>

      <h2>Where I Have Been</h2>
      <p>
        Over the years, I have traveled across a range of destinations, learning what actually makes a place
        memorable to me. It is rarely just what you see. It is how you experience it, from the meals and
        moments to the people you meet along the way.
      </p>
      <p>
        From iconic cities to smaller destinations that surprised me along the way, every trip has added
        another layer to how I explore, write, and share what is worth experiencing.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/city-guides/">Explore the City Guides</a></p>

      <h2>Where I&rsquo;m Dreaming About</h2>
      <p>
        There are still plenty of places I am excited to experience next. Some destinations stand out for their
        food, landscapes, culture, design, or simply the feeling I imagine they leave behind.
      </p>
      <p>
        Some of these destinations are already on the calendar. Others are still further out, part of a longer
        list of places I want to experience the right way.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/elevate-your-travel/where-i-am-dreaming/">See What&rsquo;s Inspiring Me</a></p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
